{
  "stem": "17426.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he called me in the first [? day ?] [? at ?] [? dawn, ?] and he made a football out of me.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He beat me left and right.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He just wanted to know who allowed me to walk out of the rows of the march, which guard.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I gave this head guard my word that no matter what, he'll never-- we will never tell him his name, that he will never be involved in this.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And so he beat and beat and beat me till finally he saw that it makes no difference.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I felt it would make no difference even if I tell him who did it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Then he ordered the same policemen, Chaim Tszan, to meet out 21 lashes on my bare behind, had to lie over the [GERMAN], which was a wooden kind of a thing.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And Tszan started to beat me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "That wasn't the kind of lashing that he expected him to do, so he took the whip out of his hand, and he showed him how to do it.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "At that point, I lost consciousness.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the next time when I came to, I was in the hall on the cement.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "My father bent over me, and a few inmates, with water trying to resuscitate me.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, his name was Tadek.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Tadeusz, was his real Polish name.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But he was called Tadek, as most Polish names were sort of made into a K-- Marek, Tadek, Josek, Branek.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was called Branek.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He knew of my meetings with Zosia, and he just closed his eyes to it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He never spoke with me about it, but I knew that he knows.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Who knew more than he was the-- the-- Gospodini, which is the kitchen person that cooked for us.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
